  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "DevOps Engineer (WFH)",
  "description": "<h3>Job Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Manage server deployment, configuration, maintenance, performance tuning, and incident response.</p></li><li><p>Responsible for service deployment, version upgrades, monitoring, and operational stability.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate closely with development and operations teams to support testing, troubleshooting, and bug resolution.</p></li><li><p>Design, build, and maintain automation tools and scripts to improve system reliability and operational efficiency.</p></li><li><p>Research, evaluate, and implement new DevOps and infrastructure technologies.</p></li><li><p>Set up, manage, and maintain <strong>Kubernetes clusters</strong>, ensuring high availability and scalability.</p></li><li><p>Support deployment strategies such as <strong>gray / canary releases</strong> (preferred).</p></li></ul><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p><strong>At least 3 years of hands-on experience</strong> in DevOps / system operations or related roles.</p></li><li><p>Strong <strong>Linux system administration</strong> skills.</p></li><li><p>Solid experience managing and maintaining distributed systems and clusters, including:<br /><strong>Elasticsearch, Nginx, RocketMQ, Redis, Nacos, MongoDB</strong></p></li><li><p>Proficient with DevOps and CI/CD tools such as <strong>SVN, Git, Jenkins, JIRA, Harbor, Nexus</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with <strong>Docker and Kubernetes</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of <strong>DevOps practices</strong> and CI/CD pipelines.</p></li><li><p>Able to write automation scripts using <strong>Python, Shell, or Ansible</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with monitoring and alerting tools such as <strong>Zabbix and Prometheus</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience with <strong>cloud infrastructure</strong>; multi-cloud exposure is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with <strong>ELK stack</strong> setup and maintenance.</p></li><li><p>Security hardening and security implementation experience is a plus.</p></li><li><p>Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work collaboratively in cross-functional teams.<br /></p><p>Business Edge Personnel Services Singapore </p><p>EA License No: 96C4864 </p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R26159908 (Tan Ying Ying)</p></li></ul>",
